    "synopsis": "Massenet's soaring score captures the intensity of young love in this tale of a beautiful young woman torn between passion and wealth. En route to a convent, Manon falls for the handsome Chevalier des Grieux and they run away to Paris together. But their youthful ardor is threatened by fatherly disapproval, and Manon finds herself choosing between waiting alone in poverty or embracing the wealth of a new lover. Music Director Eun Sun Kim conducts Vincent Boussard's cinematic production in this co-production with Lithuanian National Opera and Ballet Theatre and the Israeli Opera.",
