    "synopsis": "Composer Thea Musgrave brings one of history's most captivating figures to the operatic stage. Just 18 years old and already Queen of France, Mary Stuart returns to a Scotland she barely recognizes. As she navigates a treacherous political landscape, her closest advisors—her calculating half-brother James, the enigmatic Earl of Bothwell, and her charming but weak-willed future husband Lord Darnley—each reveal their hunger for her power in increasingly manipulative ways. Making her company debut, Clelia Cafiero conducts this co-production with English National Opera. Director and designer Stewart Laing sets 16th-century intrigue against a backdrop of contemporary Scottish life and sectarian violence, lending fresh resonance to an almost 500-year-old story.",
